%S A396963 13,19,43,131,257,1439,2351,5179,147629,291547,305407,53923301,
%T A396963 473223187,927367303
%N A396963 Last term of a 2 X n generalized arithmetic progression (GAP) of primes with smallest last term.
%C A396963 This sequence is a replacement for the incorrect A113831.
%C A396963 The 2 X k generalized arithmetic progression (GAP) of distinct primes with smallest last term is of the form a+b*i+c*j, with 0 <= i <= 1, and 0 <= j <= k-1.
%C A396963 a(n) for n = 3, 4, 5, 6, and 8 are smaller than A113831(n).
%C A396963 The list of the smallest 2 X k GAPs less than 10^9 ends at k = 15. The last term of the smallest 2 X 16 GAP will be greater than 10^9.
%H A396963 Jens Kruse Andersen, <a href="https://primerecords.dk/aprecords.htm">Primes in Arithmetic Progression Records</a> [May have candidates for later terms in this sequence.]
%H A396963 Andrew Granville, <a href="https://dms.umontreal.ca/~andrew/PDF/PrimePatterns.pdf">Prime number patterns</a>.
%e A396963 Table detailing the 2 X n GAPs, with 2 <= n <= 9:
%e A396963   n    GAP           Last term
%e A396963   2  3+8*i+2*j           13
%e A396963   3  5+2*i+6*j           19
%e A396963   4  5+2*i+12*j          43
%e A396963   5  7+4*i+30*j         131
%e A396963   6  7+100*i+30*j       257
%e A396963   7  47+132*i+210*j    1439
%e A396963   8  199+682*i+210*j   2351
%e A396963   9  199+3300*i+210*j  5179
%Y A396963 Cf. A005115, A113827, A133277, A391764, A396962.
